                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The nurse gathers data from the client who was prescribed buspirone hydrochloride 1 month ago. The nurse interprets that the medication is effective when the client reports an absence of which event?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nBuspirone hydrochloride is most often indicated for the treatment of anxiety and aggression. It is not recommended for the treatment of thought disorders (delusions), drug or alcohol cravings, or schizophrenia (paranoid thoughts).\n\nClient Needs: Physiological Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Evaluate Outcomes\nCognitive Ability: Evaluating\nContent Area: Pharmacology: Psychiatric: Antianxiety/Anxiolytics\nHealth Problem: Mental Health: Anxiety Disorder\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Evaluation\nPriority Concepts: Anxiety, Mood and Affect\nStrategies: Strategic Words, Subject\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic word, effective. Focus on the subject, buspirone hydrochloride. To answer this question accurately, you must be familiar with the classification and use of this medication. Read all four options carefully. Remember that buspirone hydrochloride is used to treat anxiety. This will direct you to the correct option.\n ",
